chapter.sb:
CF34-10E Service BulletinNo 72-0093 R01
Revised: 06/14/2019Issued: 11/15/2007
SB 72-0093 R01 ENGINE - Fan Stator Assembly (72-23-00) - Introduction of Spiral Seal Support P/N 2131M99G01

EFFECTIVITY
* * * CF34-10E
This Service Bulletin is applicable to these CF34-10E engines:
•CF34-10E engines, serial numbers 994101 through 994253, 994255 through 994259, and 994261 through 994281.
The spiral seal support P/N 2072M71G01 is affected by this Service Bulletin.
DESCRIPTION
This Service Bulletin introduces a spiral seal support P/N 2131M99G01 and provides instructions to replace the part.
BENEFIT
Improvement:
The primary difference between the proposed and current design is a material change from aluminum to a chopped glass fiber epoxy sheet-molding compound (meets MIL-M-46069). The new design will improve the producibility of the spiral seal support and reduce the manufacturing cost.
COMPLIANCE
Category 7
GE recommends that you do this Service Bulletin at customer's convenience.
MANPOWER
No additional man-hours are required to comply with this Service Bulletin.

CF34-10E Service BulletinNo 72-0326 R01

SB 72-0326 R01 ENGINE - Core Module Major Components (72-00-02)- Introduction of a New Compressor Rotor Assembly P/N 2205M31G03 with a New Blade Tip Clearance

EFFECTIVITY
* * * CF34-10E
This Service Bulletin is applicable to these CF34-10E engines:
•CF34-10E engines, serial numbers 994111 through 994999 and 424101 through 424733.
This Service Bulletin has been introduced in production to these CF34-10E engines:
•CF34-10E engines, serial numbers 424734 and up.
These serial numbers are the best available data.

This Service Bulletin releases a new compressor rotor assembly P/N 2205M31G03, which has new tip grind radius dimensions for the compressor rotor stages 3, 5, and 6 blades.
BENEFIT
Improvement:
The new tip grind radius dimensions will reduce the compressor rotor blade tip rub levels on stages 3, 5, and 6. This will reduce the blade material deposit on the compressor flow path.
COMPLIANCE
 Category 5

EFFECTIVITY
* * * CF34-10E
This Service Bulletin is applicable to these CF34-10E engines:
•CF34-10E engines, serial numbers 994111, 994113 through 994999, and 424101 through 424736.
This Service Bulletin has been introduced in production to these CF34-10E engines:
•CF34-10E engines, serial numbers 424737 and up.

These serial numbers are the best available data.
The air turbine starter VIN 3505953-4 (P/N 4120T06P04) is affected by this Service Bulletin.
DESCRIPTION
This Service Bulletin provides instructions to rework the affected air turbine starter to the new VIN 3505953-6 (P/N 4120T06P10) configuration.
BENEFIT
Improvement:
Refer to the attached Honeywell Service Bulletin 3505953-80-1885 (latest version).
COMPLIANCE
Category 6
GE recommends that you do this Service Bulletin when the affected air turbine starter is routed for repair.
MANPOWER
No additional man-hours are required to comply with this Service Bulletin.
